\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Finally, making the best of circumstances, Cugel set himself to wait upon the clerk's convenience.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The outer door opened; into the chamber came a man of Cugel's o
wn age, wearing a tall-crowned hat of brown felt and a rumpled suit of blue velvet. His face was round and placid; tufts of pale hair like wisps of hay protruded from under his hat. His belly pressed forward the front of his coat, and a pair of broad butt
ocks rode upon two long spindle-shanked legs.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
