culty we will arrive at Lausicaa, and there make adjustments."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Captain Baunt had already altered course toward Lausicaa, so that Madame Soldinck might bathe in the Paphnissian Springs. Baunt, who had hoped to make a quick passage, was not happy with the delay, and }{
\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid15211943 watched Cugel closely, to make s}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
ure that the worms were used to the maximum efficiency. "Cugel!" called Captain Baunt. "Adjust the lead on that off-worm; it is pulling us broadside!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Aye, sir."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 And presently: "Cugel! Your starboard worm is listless; it merely slaps the water. Freshen its bait!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "I am already at double-bait," grumbled Cugel. "It was fresh an hour ago."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Then use half a gill of Heidinger's Allure, and be quick about it! I wish to make Pompodouros before sunset tomorrow!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 During the 
night the starboard worm, becoming fretful, began to slap at the water with its flukes. Drofo, aroused by the splashing, came up from his cabin. Leaning on the rail he watched as Cugel ran back and forth along the sponson, trying to throw a check-line ove
r the mischievous worm's flukes.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 After a few moments observation, Drofo diagnosed the problem. He called out in a nasal voice: "Always lift the bait before throwing a check-line. . . Now then, what is happening down there?"}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel responded sullenly: "The worm wants to swim up, down and sideways."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "What did you feed?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "The usual: half Chalcorex and half Illem's Best."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "You might use a bit less Chalcorex for the next day or so. That lump of tissue behind the turret is usually a dependable signal. How did you bait?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Double-bait, as I was instructed. The captain ordered a further half-gill of Heidinger's Allure."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "There is your problem. You have over-baited, which is an act of folly."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "At Captain Baunt's orders!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "That excuse is worse than none. Who is the wormi
nger, you or Captain Baunt? You know your worms; you must work them by the dictates of your experience and good judgment. If Baunt interferes, ask him to come down and advise you in regard to an infestation of gangue. That is the way of the worminger! Cha
nge bait at once and drench the worm with a seep of Blagin's Mulcent."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Very good, sir," said Cugel between his teeth.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Drofo made a brief survey of sky and horizon, then returned to his cabin and Cugel busied himself with the drench.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Captain Baunt had order
ed the sail set, hoping to catch a waft of favorable air. Two hours after midnight a cross-wind arose, causing the sail to flap against the mast, creating a dismal sound which aroused Captain Baunt from his slumber. Baunt lurched out on deck. "Where is th
e watch? Hoy! Worminger! You there! Is no one about?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel, clambering up to the deck from the sponson, replied: "Only the lookout, who is asleep under the lantern."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Well then, what of you? Why have you not silenced that sail? Are you deaf?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid15211943 "No sir. I have been unde}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 r-water, drenching with Blagin's Mulcent."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Well then, heave aft}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid15211943  on the leach-line, and abate that cursed}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278  slatting!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 

\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel hastened to obey, while Captain Baunt went to the starboard rail. Here he discovered new cause for dissatisfaction. "Worminger, where is your bait? I ordered double-bait, with aroma of Allure!"}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Sir, one cannot drench while the worm exerts itself for bait."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Why then did you drench? }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid8748279 I}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278  ordered no Mulcent!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel drew himself up. "Sir, I drenched that worm according to the dictates of my best judgment and experience."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
