\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Captain Baunt called out again: "Drofo, muffle your worms!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Muffle worms!" came Drofo's response, and then: "Cugel, muffles all around! Quick now!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel muffled the starboard worm, but fell into the water and was slow with the port muffles, prompting a complaint}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid5471861  from Captain Baunt. "Drofo, hurry the muff}{
\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 les! Are you conducting a rite for the dead? Boatswain, ready the anchor!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Muffles going on!" sang out Drofo. "Look sharp, Cugel!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Anchor at the ready, sir."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The worms were muffled at last, and the }{\b0\i\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Galante }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 barely drifted through the water.}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Let go the anchor!" called Captain Baunt.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Anchor in the water, sir! Bottom at six fathoms."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The }{\b0\i\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Galante }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
lay placidly to anchor. Cugel eased the worms in their cinctures, applied unguent and fed each worm a measure of victual.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 After the evening meal Captain Baunt assembled the ship's company on the midship de}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid5471861 ck. Standing halfway up the com}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
panionway ladder he spoke a few words in regard to Lausicaa and the town Pompodouros.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Those of you who have visited this place before, I doubt if there are many, will understand why I must issue warnings. In a nut-shell, you wi
ll find certain customs which guide the folk of this island to be at variance with our own. They may impress you as strange, grotesque, laughable, disgraceful, picturesque or commendable, depending upon your point of view. Whatever the case, we must take 
note of these customs and abide by them, since the folk of Lausicaa will definitely not alter their ways in favor of ours."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Captain Baunt smilingly acknowledged the presence of Madame Soldinck and her three daughters. "My remarks apply almost exclusively to
 the gentlemen aboard, and if I touch upon topics which might be considered tasteless, I can only plead necessity; so I beg your indulgence!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Soldinck cried out bluffly: "Enough of your breast-beating, Baunt! Speak up! We are all reasonable people aboard, Madame Soldinck included!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
Captain Baunt waited until the laughter had died down. "Very well then! Look along the dock yonder; you will notice three persons standing under the street-lamp. All are men. The faces of each are hidden behind hoods and veils. F
or this precaution there is reason; the ebullience of the local females. So vivacious is their nature that men dare not display their faces for}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid5471861  }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
fear of provoking ungovernable impulses. Female voyeurs go so far as to peek through windows of the clubhouse where the men gather to drink beer, sometimes with their faces partially exposed."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 At this information Madame Soldinck and her daughters laughed nervously. "Extraordinary!" said Madame Soldinck. "And women of every social class act in this fashion?"}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Absolutely!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Meadhre asked diffidently: "Do the men propose marriage with their faces concealed?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Captain Baunt reflected. "So far as }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid8748279 I}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278  know, the idea never enters anyone's head."}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "It does not seem a wholesome atmosphere in which to bring up children," said Madame Soldinck.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
"Apparently the children are not seriously affected," said Captain Baunt. "Until the age of ten boys may sometimes be seen bare-faced, but even during these tender years they are protected from adventurous young females. At the age of ten they 
'go under the veil', to use the local idiom."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "How tiresome for the girls!" sighed Salasser.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "And also undignified!" said Tabazinth with emphasis. "Suppose I noticed what appeared to be a handsome young man, and ran after him and finally subdued him, and t
hen, when I pulled away his hood, I found protruding yellow teeth, a big nose and a narrow receding forehead. What next? I would feel a fool simply getting up and walking away."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Meadhre suggested: "You could tell the gentleman that you merely wanted directions back to the ship."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Whatever the case," Captain Baunt went on, "the women of Lausicaa have evolved techniques to restore the equilibrium. After this fashion:}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "The men are partial to spraling, which are small delicate bidechtils. They swim at the surfa
ce of the sea in the early morning. The women, therefore, arise in the pre-dawn hours, wade out into the sea, where they capture as much spraling as possible, then return to their huts.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Those women with a good catch set their fires going and hang out signs, such as: FINE SPRALING TODAY, or TASTY SPRALING TO YOUR ORDER."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4023646 "The men arise in due course and}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278  stroll about t}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4023646 h}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
e town. When at last they work up an appetite, they stop by a hut where the sign offers refreshment to their taste. Often, if the spraling is fresh and the company good, they may stay for dinner as well."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 

\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Madame Soldinck sniffed and murmured aside to her daughters, who merely shrugged and shook their heads.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
