be taken lightly! When you go ashore, wear a robe or a loose gown and by some means muffle your face so as to avoid any unseemly or improper incident! Am }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid8748279 I}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278  clear?"}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Captain Baunt said: "In the morning we will moor at the dock and attend to our various items
 of business. Drofo, I suggest that you put this interval to good purpose. Anoint your animals well and cure all chafes, galls and cankers. Exercise them daily about the harbor,}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4023646  since idleness brings on impacti}{
\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 on. Cure all your infestations; trim all gills. These hours in port are precious; each must be used to the fullest, without regard for day or night."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "This echoes my own thinking," said Drofo. "I will immediately give the necessary orders to Cugel."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
