g toward hostile intruders, thus securing the caravan against night-wandering hoons, erbs and grues.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Once again a great fire was built, with wood broken from the deodars. The 'premier' passengers partook of three preliminary courses served by Porraig aboard the }{
\b0\i\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Avventura, }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 then joined the 'ordinaries' for bread, stew and sour greens around the fire.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Varmous served wine, but with a hand less lavish than on the previous evening.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 After supper Varmous addressed the g}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid8271463 roup. "As everyone knows, we ha}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 ve made a detou
r, which should cause us neither inconvenience nor, so I trust, delay. Ho}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid8271463 wever, we now travel the Ildish }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
Waste, a land which is strange to me. I feel compelled to take special safeguards. You will notice the guard-fence, which is intended to deter intruders."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
