\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Clissum stood with a pained smile frozen on his face, then turned away and resumed his seat.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 A wind blew down from the north, causing the flame
s to leap and the smoke to billow, Ivanello cried out a light-hearted curse. He put down his lute and began to toy with the mimes, whom, as before, he had hypnotized with his music. Tonight he became bolder in his caresses, and encountered no protest so l
ong as he evenly shared his attentions.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel watched with disapproval. He muttered to Doctor Lalanke: "Ivanello is persuading your wards to laxity."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
