ur, while the pre-dawn sky still glowed purple. Porraig the steward served a breakfast of tea, scones and a savory mince of clams, barley, kangol and pennywort. As usual, Nissifer failed to make an appearance and this morning Ivanello was missing as well.
}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Porraig called down to Varmous, suggesting that he send Ivanello aboard for his breakfast, but a survey of the camp yielded nothing. Ivanello's possessions occupied their ordinary}{
