\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The creature took a step forward. Shilko emitted a strangled yell and, stumbling backwards, fell to the deck. The creature jumped forward to stand on his arms, then, s
quatting, drove its sting into his chest. Shilko uttered a shrill cry, rolled clear, turned several frantic somersaults, fell to the ground, bounded blindly to the lake and thrashed here and there in the water, and at last became still. Almost at once the
 corpse began to bloat.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Aboard the }{\b0\i\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Avventura, }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
the creature named Nissifer turned and started to re-enter the cabin, as if satisfied that it had rebuffed its enemies. Cugel, on the afterdeck, slashed down with his sword and the blade, trailing a thousand spa
rkling motes, cut through Nissifer's left eye and into the thorax. Nissifer whistled in pain and surprise, and stood back the better to identify its assailant. It croaked: "Ah Cugel! You have hurt me; you shall die by a stench."}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 With a great pounding flutt
er of wing-cases, Nissifer sprang up to the afterdeck. In a panic Cugel retreated behind the binnacle. Nissifer advanced, the segmented abdomen squirming up and forward between the thin black legs, revealing the long yellow sting.}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel picked up one of th
e empty buckets and flung it into Nissifer's face; then, while Nissifer fought away the bucket, Cugel jumped forward and with a great sweep, cut the vincus, so as to separate abdomen from thorax.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The abdomen, falling to the deck, writhed and worked and presently rolled down the companion-way to the deck.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Nissifer ignored the mutilation and came forward, dripping}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid675855  a thick yellow liquid from its vincus.  It lurched toward the binnacle }{
\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 and thrust out its long black arms. Cugel backed away, hacking at the arms. Nissifer shrieked and lunging forward, swept the sword from Cugel's grasp.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Nissifer stepped forward with clicking wing-cases, and seizing Cugel, drew him close. "Now, Cugel, you will learn the meaning of fetor."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel bent his head and thrust 'Spatterlight' against Nissifer's thorax.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 When Varmous, sword in hand, climbed the companion-way, he found Cugel leaning limp-legged against the taff-rail.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Varmous looked around the afterdeck. "Where is Nissifer?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Nissifer is gone."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Four days later the caravan ca}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid675855 me down from the hills to the sh}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
ores of Lake Zaol. Across the glimmering water eight white towers half-hidden in pink haze}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid675855  marked the site of Kaspara Vit}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 atus, sometimes known as 'The City of Monuments.'}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The caravan circled the lake and approached the city by the Avenue of the Dynasties. After passing under a hundred or more of the famous monume}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid675855 
nts, the caravan arrived at the}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278  center of town. Varmous led the way to his usual resort, the Kanbaw Inn, and the weary travelers prepared to refresh themselves.}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 While orde
ring the cabin occupied by Nissifer, Cugel had come upon a leather sack containing over a hundred terces, which he took into his private possession. Varmous, however, insisted upon helping Cugel explore the effects of I}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid675855 
vanello, Er}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 maulde, and Perruquil. The
y discovered another three hundred terces which they shared in equal parts. Varmous took possession of Ivanello's wardrobe, while Cugel was allowed to keep the milk-opal ear-bangle, which he had coveted from the first.}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel also offered Varmous full title to the }{\b0\i\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Avventura }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
for five hundred terces. "The price is an absolute bargain! Where else will you find a sound vessel, fully outfitted and well-found, for such a price?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Varmous only chuckled. "If you offered to provide me a goiter of superlative size for ten terces, would I buy, bargain or not?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "We have here a distinctly different proposition," Cugel pointed out.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Bah! The magic is failing. Every day the ship sags more heavily to the ground. In the middle of the wilderness what good is a ship which will n
either float in the air nor sail in the sand? In a foolhardy spirit, I will offer you a hundred terces, no more."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Absurd!" scoffed Cugel, and there the matter rested.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Varmous went out to see to the repair of his wagons and discovered a pair of lake fishermen inspecting the }{\b0\i\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Avventura }{
\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 with interest. In due course Varmous succeeded in obtaining a firm offer for the vessel, to the amount of six hundred and twenty-five terces.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel, meanwhile, drank beer at the Kanbaw Inn. As he sat musing, into the common roo
m strode a band of seven men with harsh features and rough voices. Cugel looked twice at the leader, then a third time, and}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid675855  finally recognized Captain Wis}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
kich, one-time owner of the }{\b0\i\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Avventura. }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Captain Wiskich evidently had picked up the trail of the vessel
 and had come in hot pursuit to recover his property.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel quietly departed the common room and went in search of Varmous, who, as it happened, was also on the lookout for Cugel. They met in front of the inn. Varmous wanted to drink beer in the common roo
m, but Cugel led him across the avenue to a bench from which they could watch the sun set into Lake Zaol.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Presently the }{\b0\i\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Avventura }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
was mentioned and with surprising ease agreement was reached. Varmous paid over two hundred and fifty terces for full title to the vessel.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The two parted on the best of terms. Varmous went off to locate the fishermen, while Cugel, disguising himself in a hooded cloak and a false beard, took l}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid675855 
odging at the Green }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Star Inn, using the identity Tichenor, a purveyor of antique grave-markers.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
During the evening a great tumult was heard, first from the neighborhood of the docks and then at the Kanbaw Inn, and persons coming into the Green Star common room identified the rioters as a group of local fishermen in conflict with a band}{
\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid675855  }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid8532196\charrsid3035278 of}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278  newly arrived travelers, with the eventual involvement }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid8532196\charrsid3035278 of}{
\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278  Varmous and his teamsters.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Order was restored at last. Not long after, two men looked into the Green Star common room. One called out in a rough voice: "Is there anyone here named Cugel?"}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The other spoke with more restraint: "Cugel is urgently needed. If he is here, let him step forward."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 When no one responded the two men departed and Cugel retired to his room.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 In the morning Cugel went to a nearby hostlery where he purchased a steed for his journey sout
h. The ostler's boy then conducted him to a shop where Cugel bought a new pouch, a pair of saddle-bags into which he packed necessities for his journey. His hat had become shabby and also carried a stench where it had pressed against Nissifer. Cugel remov
ed 'Spatter-light', wrapped it in heavy cloth and tucked it into his new pouch. He bought a short-billed cap of dark green velvet, which, while far from ostentatious, pleased Cugel with its air of restrained elegance.}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel paid his account from the terces in the leather sack from Nissifer's cabin; it also exhaled a stench. Cugel started to buy a new sack but was dissuaded by the ostler's boy. "Why waste your terces? }{
\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid8748279 I}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278  have a sack much like this one which you may have free of charge."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "That is generous of you," said Cugel, and the two returned to the hostlery, where Cugel transferred his terces into the new sack.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The steed was brought forth. Cugel mounted and the boy adjusted the saddle-bags in place. At this moment two men of harsh appearance entered the hos
tlery, and approached with quick strides. "Is your name Cugel?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Definitely not!" declared Cugel. "By no means! I am Tichenor! What do you want with this Cugel?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "None of your affair. Come along with us; you have an unconvincing manner."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "I have no time fo
r pranks," said Cugel. "Boy, you may hand me up my leather sack." The boy obeyed and Cugel secured the sack to his saddle. He started to ride away but the men interfered. "You must come with us."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Impossible," said Cugel. "I am on my way to Torqual." He kicked one in the nose and the other in the belly and rode at speed down the Avenue of th}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid273486 
e Dynasties and so departed Kas}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 para Vitatus.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 After a period he halted, to learn what pursuit, if any, had been offered.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 An unpleasant odor reached his nostrils, emanating from the leather sack. To his perplexity, it proved to be the same sack he had taken from Nissifer's cabin.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 

\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel anxiously looked within, to find, not terces, but small objects of corroded metal.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel uttered a groan of dismay and, turning his steed, started to return to Kaspara Vitatus, but now he noticed a dozen men crouched low in their saddles coming after him in hot pursuit.}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel uttered another wild cry of fury and frustration. He cast the leather sack into the ditch and turning his steed once more rode south at full speed.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 

