\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The asm spoke in a soft blurred voice: "Wrong! You carry an ordinary pebble. I watched and you scamped the rite. Flee if you wish! I need the exercise."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The asm advanced. Cugel threw the stone with all his force. It struck the black forehead between the bristling antennae, and the asm fell flat; before it could rise Cugel had severed its head.}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 He started to proceed, then turned back and took up the stone. "Who knows who guided the throw so accurately? Wiulio deserves the benefit of the doubt."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 At the first Sarsen he exchanged stones as Erwig had recommended, and this time he made the trigrammatic sign with care and precision.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Without interference he crossed to the next sarsen and so continued across the plain.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The sun made its way to the zenith, rested a period, then descended into the west. Cugel marched unmolested from sarsen to sarsen. On several occasions he noted pelgrane sliding}{
\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid11994911  }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 across the sky, and each time flung himself flat to avoid attention.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The Plain of Standing Stones ended at the brink of a scarp overlooking a wide valley. With }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid11994911 safety close at hand Cugel }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid8532196 rel}{
\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid8532196\charrsid3035278 a}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid8532196 x}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid8532196\charrsid3035278 ed}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
 his vigilance, only to be startled by a scream of triumph from the sky. He darted a horrified glance over his shoulder, then plunged over the edge of the scarp into a ravine, where he dodged among rocks and pressed himself }{
