 no more time! Let us hasten into Cuirnif and seek out the}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid874205  }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 scoundrel who stole my valuables."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The road left the forest and passed through a district of fields and orchards. Peasants looked up in wonder as the two passed by: the portly }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid11994911 Iolo}{
\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278  dressed in black and white diaper and the lank Cugel with a black cloak hanging from his spare shoulders and a fine dark green cap gracing his saturnine visage.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 

\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Along the way }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid11994911 Iolo}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278  put ever more searching questions in regard to the robber. Cugel had lost interest in the su
bject and gave back ambiguous, even contradictory, answers, and }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid11994911 Iolo}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 's questions became ever more searching.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Upon entering Cuirnif, Cugel noticed an inn which seemed to offer comfortable accommodation. He told }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid11994911 Iolo}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
: "Here our paths diverge, since I plan to stop at the inn yonder."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "The Five Owls? It is the dearest inn of Cuirnif! How will you pay your account?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel made a confident gesture. "Is not a thousand terces the grand prize at the Exposition?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Certainly, but what marvel do you plan to display? I warn you, the Duke has no patience with charlatans."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "I am not a man who tells all he knows," said Cugel. "I will disclose none of my plans at this moment."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "But what of the robber?" cried }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid11994911 Iolo}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 . "Were we not to search Cuirnif high and low?"}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "The Five Owls 
is as good a vantage as any, since the robber will surely visit the common room to boast of his exploits and squander your terces on drink. Meanwhile, I wish you easy roofs and convenient dreams." Cugel bowed politely and took his leave of }{
\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid11994911 Iolo}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 .}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 At the Five Owls Cugel selected a suitable chamber, where he refreshed himself and ordered his attire. Then, repairing to}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid874205  }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
the common room, he made a leisurely meal upon the best the house could provide.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The innkeeper stopped by to make sure that all was in order and
 Cugel complimented him upon his table. "In fact, all taken with all, Cuirnif must be considered a place favored by the elements. The prospect is pleasant, the air is bracing, and Duke Orbal would seem to be an indulgent ruler."}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The innkeeper gave a somewh
at noncommital assent. "As you indicate, Duke Orbal is never exasperated, truculent, suspicious, nor harsh unless in his wisdom he feels so inclined, whereupon all mildness is put aside in the interests of justice. Glance up to the crest of the hill; what
 do you see?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Four tubes, or stand-pipes, approximately thirty yards tall and one yard in diameter."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Your eye is accurate. Into these tubes are dropped insubordinate members of society, without regard for who stands below or who may be coming after. Hence
, while you may converse with Duke Orbal or even venture a modest pleasantry, never ignore his commands. Criminals, of course, are given short shrift."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel, from habit, looked uneasily over his shoulder. "Such strictures will hardly apply to me, a stranger in town."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The innkeeper gave a skeptical grunt. "I assume that you came to witness the Exposition of Marvels?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Quite so! I may even try for the grand prize. In this regard, can you recommend a dependable hostler?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Certainly." The innkeeper provided explicit directions.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid8748279 I}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278  also wish to hire a gang of strong and willing workers," said Cugel. "Where may these be recruited?"}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The innkeeper pointed across the square to a dingy tavern. "In the yard of the 'Howling Dog' all the riffraff in town take counsel together. Here you will find workers sufficient to your purposes."}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "While I visit the hostler, be good enough to send a boy across to hire twelve of these sturdy fellows."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "As you wish."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 At the hostler's Cugel rented a large six-wheeled wagon and a team of s
trong farlocks. When he returned with the wagon to the Five Owls, he found waiting a work-force of twelve individuals of miscellaneous sort, including a man not only senile but also lacking a leg. Another, in the throes of intoxication, fought away imagin
ary insects. Cugel discharged these two on the spot. The group also included }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid11994911 Iolo}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278  the Dream-taker, who scrutinized Cugel with the liveliest suspicion.}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel asked: "My dear fellow, what do you do in such sordid company?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "I take employment so that I may eat," said }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid11994911 Iolo}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
. "May I ask how you came by the funds to pay for so much skilled labor? Also, I notice that from your ear hangs that gem which only last night was my property!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "It is the second of a pair," said Cugel. "As you know, the robber took the first along with your other valuables."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid11994911 Iolo}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278  curled his lips. "I am more than ever anxious to meet this quixotic robber who takes my gem but leaves you in possession of yours."}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "He was indeed a remarkable person. I believe that I glimpsed him not an hour ago, riding hard out of town."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid11994911 Iolo}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278  again curled his lip. "What do you propose to do with this wagon?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "If you care to earn a wage, you will soon find out for yourself."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel drove the wagon and the gang of workers out of Cuirnif along the road to the mysterious
 hole, where he found all as before. He ordered trenches dug into the hillside; crating was installed, after which that block of soil surrounding and including the hole, the stump and the tentacle, was dragged up on the bed of the wagon.}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 During the middle stages of the project }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid11994911 Iolo}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
's manner changed. He began calling orders to the workmen and addressed Cugel with cordiality. "A noble idea, Cugel! We shall profit greatly!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel raised his eyebrows. "I hope indeed to win the grand prize. Your wage, however, will be relatively modest, even scant, unless you work more briskly."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 

\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "What!" stormed }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid11994911 Iolo}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 . "Surely you agree that this hole is half my property!"}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "I agree to nothing of the sort. Say no more of the matter, or you will be discharged on the spot."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Grumbling and fuming }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid11994911 Iolo}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
 returned to work. In due course Cugel conveyed the block of soil, with the hole, stump and tentacle, back to Cuirnif. Along the way he purchased an old tarpaulin with which he concealed the hole, the better to magnify the eventual effect of his display.}
{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
At the site of the Grand Exposition Cugel slid his exhibit off the wagon and into the shelter of a pavilion, after which he paid off his men, to the dissatisfaction of those who had cultivated extravagant hopes.}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel refused to listen to complaints. "The pay is sufficient! If it were ten times as much, every last terce would still end up in the till at the 'Howling Dog'."}{
\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "One moment!" cried }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid11994911 Iolo}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 . You and I must arrive at an understanding!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 

\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Cugel merely jumped up on the wagon and drove it back to the hostelry. Some of the men pursued him a few steps; others threw stones, without effect.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 On the following day trumpets and gongs announced the formal opening of the exposition. Duke Orbal arrived at the plaza wearing a splendid robe of magenta plus
h trimmed with white feathers, and a hat of pale blue velvet three feet in diameter, with silver tassels around the brim and a cockade of silver puff.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Mounting a rostrum, Duke Orbal addressed the crowd. "As all know, I am considered an eccentric, what with
 my enthusiasm for marvels and prodigies, but, after all, when the preoccupation is analyzed, is it all so absurd? Think back across the aeons to the times of the Vapurials, the Green and Purple College, the mighty magicians among whose number we include 
Amberlin, the second }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid874205 Chidule of Porphyrhyncos, Morre}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
ion, Calanctus the Calm, and of course the Great Phandaal. These were the days of power, and they are not likely to return except in nostalgic recollection. Hence this, my Grand Exposition of Marvels, and 
withal, a pale recollection of the way things were.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Still, all taken with all, I see by my schedule that we have a stimulating program, and no doubt I will find difficulty in awarding the grand prize."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Duke Orbal glanced at a paper. "We will inspect Zaraflam's}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4354669  }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
'Nimble Squadrons', Bazzard's 'Unlikely Musicians', Xallops and his 'Compendium of Universal Knowledge', }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid11994911 Iolo}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
 will offer his 'Bagful of Dreams', and, finally, Cugel will present for our amazement that to which he gives the tantalizing title: 'Nowhere
'. A most provocative program! And now without further ado we will proceed to evaluate Zaraflam's 'Nimble Squadrons'."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The crowd surged around the first pavilion and Zaraflam brought forth his 'Nimble Squadrons': a parade of cockroaches smartly turned out 
in red, white, and black uniforms. The sergeants brandished cutlasses; the foot soldiers carried muskets; the squadrons marched and countermarched in intricate evolutions.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Halt!" bawled Zaraflam.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The cockroaches stopped short.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Present arms!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The cockroaches obeyed.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Fire a salute in honor of Duke Orbal!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The sergeants raised their cutlasses; the footmen elevated their muskets. Down came the cutlasses; the muskets exploded, emitting little puffs of white smoke.}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 

\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "Excellent!" declared Duke Orbal. "Zaraflam, I commend your painstaking accuracy!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "A thousand thanks, your Grace! Have I won the grand prize?"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 "It is still too early to predict. Now, to Bazzard and his 'Unlikely Musicians'!"}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 The spectators moved on to the second pavilion where Bazzard presently appe
ared, his face woebegone. "Your Grace and noble citizens of Cuirnif! My 'Unlikely Musicians' were fish from the Cantic Sea and I felt sure of the grand prize when I brought them to Cuirnif. However, during the night a leak drained the tank dry. The fish a
re dead and their music is lost forever! I still wish to remain in contention for the prize; hence I will simulate the songs of my former troupe. Please adjudicate the music on this basis."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Duke Orbal made an austere sign. "Impossible. Bazzard's exhibit is hereby declared invalid. We now move on to Xallops and his remarkable 'Compendium'."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Xallops stepped forward from his pavilion. "Your Grace, ladies and gentlemen of Cuirnif! My entry at this exposition is truly remarkable; however, unlike Zaraflam and Bazz
ard, I can take no personal credit for its}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4354669  existence. By trade I am a ran}{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
sacker of ancient tombs, where the risks are great and rewards few. By great good luck I chanced upon that crypt where several aeons ago the sorcerer Zinqzin was laid to rest. From th
is dungeon I rescued the volume which I now display to your astounded eyes."}{\b0\f54\fs24\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 
\par }{\b0\f54\fs24\cf1\insrsid4274412\charrsid3035278 Xallops whisked away cloth to reveal a great book bound in black leather. "On command this volume must reveal information of any and every sort; it knows each trivial detail, from
